 <br>
The media resources web page concept has been approved by the Congressional team, and the beta page is ready to fly!  Content is now needed to start filling the page.  After representative entries are loaded into the page, the beta version will be examined by the Congressional Team, and when approved, the page will be available to all.  Here is what is needed to make this happen.<br>
 <br>
1. Initially, information about news relevant to rocketry (in the context of the iniative) should be sent to the web page via e-mail at the following address:<br>
 <br>
submissions@iexrs.org<br>
 <br>
<br>
2. Please include in the subject line of the submission, what type of submission is being transmitted.  Examples of types of submissions desired ASAP include (see also point #5, below):<br>
 <br>
a) Newspaper article<br>
b) Magazine article<br>
c) Video broadcast<br>
d) Links to other information pages<br>
e) Rocketry organizations and their contact information<br>
 <br>
3. Please send only one type of submission per e-mail message.  For example, if one has four newspaper article links, and one television news program link, two e-mails are requested.  The first, with the subject title ?newspaper article links? would have the four article links in the body of the message.  The second, with the subject title ?TV news video link? would have the one video link in the body of the message.<br>
 <br>
4. If a link is not available, please attempt to ascertain whether the owner of the information will allow a reposting of the article, video, etc., to this web page, and what type of credit must be assigned.  If the entity you ascertain this information from sends you e-mail approval, please forward that as well as the article to submissions@iexrs.org.<br>
 <br>
5. MANY more types of entries will be solicited for the webpage.  Lists of potential interviewees by state, state-by-state reports of affected businesses, photos of/stories about &quot;familyish&quot; launches, letters of support from businesses and rocketeers, a media ready-to-hand executive summary, and technical articles with point-counter-point are examples of the additional types of entries that are being considered.  If these types of entries are already at-hand, please send them to submissions@iexrs.org with the appropriate label in the subject line, ASAP.  Additional information will be posted in real time.<br>
 <br>
6. The dudes who have both become ill due to no sleep and constant effort on this particular project are Gonzalo Ortega and Ismaeel Abdur-Rasheed, both of whom are rocketeers and professionals in the computer industry.  High-five, men!<br>
 <br>
7. Technical expertise (e.g., graphic display) may be solicited to assist in some aspects of this page.  When and if that becomes a reality, a call will be placed via forum announcement requesting a volunteer.<br>
 <br>
8. This page could be ready to go into production mode in as little as 24 hours, so please start posting material from points #2 and #5 now!<br>
 <br>
GET THE WORD OUT PLEASE<br>
<br>
we don't know where a TV or News piece will show up next, so everyone has to know that when they see it, send it into submissions@iexrs.org<br>
<br>
thanks!<br>
<br>
- iz<br>
